(2006)
</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8BD20F16A067FFC7FF08FACFD6F0F8B4" blockId="9.[164,779,1299,1903]" pageId="9" pageNumber="828">
We propose the name 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D7495A067FFC7FE0BFACFD785FA22" authority="Gil Collado, 1930: 254" authorityName="Gil Collado" authorityPageNumber="254" authorityYear="1930" baseAuthorityName="Gil Collado" baseAuthorityYear="1930" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Merodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="828" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bicolor">
<emphasis id="B919D304A067FFC7FE0BFACFD57BFA02" box="[447,563,1391,1413]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="828">M. bicolor</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFFC72E7A067FFC7FD88FAD0D785FA22" author="Gil Collado J" pageId="9" pageNumber="828" refId="ref8134" refString="Gil Collado J. 1930. Monografia de los sirfidos de Espana. Madrid: Trabajos del M. N. C. N. Serie Zoologica, n ° 54." type="book" year="1930">Gil Collado, 1930: 254</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="4C6D7495A067FFC7FF51FA31D601FA25" authorityName="Meigen" authorityYear="1803" box="[229,329,1422,1443]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Merodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="828" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B919D304A067FFC7FF51FA31D601FA25" box="[229,329,1422,1443]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="828">Merodon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, as var. of 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D7495A067FFC7FE52FA31D50AFA25" baseAuthorityName="Fabricius" baseAuthorityYear="1794" box="[486,578,1422,1443]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Merodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="828" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spinipes">
<emphasis id="B919D304A067FFC7FE52FA31D50AFA25" box="[486,578,1422,1443]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="828">spinipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) (identity: valid species: comb. nov.) for the cryptic taxon from the Iberian Peninsula. 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D7495A067FFC7FE25FA74D51AFA66" authorityName="Gil Collado" authorityYear="1930" baseAuthorityName="Gil Collado" baseAuthorityYear="1930" box="[401,594,1483,1504]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Merodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="828" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bicolor">
<emphasis id="B919D304A067FFC7FE25FA74D51AFA66" box="[401,594,1483,1504]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="828">Merodon bicolor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described from the 
<specimenCount id="9D6BC49FA067FFC7FEA8FA55D683FA79" box="[284,459,1514,1536]" pageId="9" pageNumber="828" type="generic" typeStatus="syntypes">three syntypes</specimenCount>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFFC72E7A067FFC7FE56FA55D5F2F986" author="Gil Collado J" box="[482,698,1514,1536]" pageId="9" pageNumber="828" refId="ref8134" refString="Gil Collado J. 1930. Monografia de los sirfidos de Espana. Madrid: Trabajos del M. N. C. N. Serie Zoologica, n ° 54." type="book" year="1930">Gil Collado, 1930</bibRefCitation>
), as a variety of 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D7495A067FFC7FE9AF9B6D501F998" authority="(Fabricius)" baseAuthorityName="Fabricius" baseAuthorityYear="1794" box="[302,585,1544,1566]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Merodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="828" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spinipes">
<emphasis id="B919D304A067FFC7FE9AF9B6D6F2F998" box="[302,442,1545,1566]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="828">M. spinipes</emphasis>
(Fabricius)
</taxonomicName>
from following localities: El Escorial, Cazzurro, Cercedilla, Arias, Somosiera, G. Menor. In depositary museum (Instituto Español de Entomología, 
<collectingRegion id="49A9C1F4A067FFC7FDA0F9DBD523F9FC" box="[532,619,1636,1658]" country="Spain" name="Madrid" pageId="9" pageNumber="828">Madrid</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F37A4F86A067FFC7FDC8F9DBD589F9FC" box="[636,705,1636,1658]" name="Spain" pageId="9" pageNumber="828">Spain</collectingCountry>
), only 
<specimenCount id="9D6BC49FA067FFC7FF10F93CD665F91E" box="[164,301,1667,1688]" pageId="9" pageNumber="828" type="generic" typeStatus="syntype">one syntype</specimenCount>
was found. Based on this type specimen, the 
<typeStatus id="54D6B1B4A067FFC7FF6EF91ED608F931" box="[218,320,1697,1719]" pageId="9" pageNumber="828">lectotype</typeStatus>
of this taxon was designated here: male ‘s 
<emphasis id="B919D304A067FFC7FF47F97FD60DF953" box="[243,325,1728,1749]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="828">pinipes</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C6D7495A067FFC7FEF8F97FD6F9F953" authorityName="Gil Collado" authorityYear="1930" box="[332,433,1728,1749]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Merodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="828" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="variety" species="spinipes" variety="bicolor">
v. 
<emphasis id="B919D304A067FFC7FED0F97FD6F9F953" box="[356,433,1728,1749]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="828">bicolor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
/ Cazurro’ (El Escorial, 
<collectingCountry id="F37A4F86A067FFC7FD74F97FD44BF950" box="[704,771,1728,1750]" name="Spain" pageId="9" pageNumber="828">Spain</collectingCountry>
) (MNCN). The 
<typeStatus id="54D6B1B4A067FFC7FEE8F961D68AF972" box="[348,450,1758,1780]" pageId="9" pageNumber="828">lectotype</typeStatus>
shared the morphological characters with specimens from 
<collectingCountry id="F37A4F86A067FFC7FD85F942D53BF895" box="[561,627,1789,1811]" name="Spain" pageId="9" pageNumber="828">Spain</collectingCountry>
analysed in this paper (
<tableCitation id="C6EF3AADA067FFC7FE98F8A3D6C3F8B7" box="[300,395,1820,1842]" captionStart="Table 1" captionStartId="3.[164,228,198,217]" captionText="Table 1. The Merodon avidus group: species, sampling sites, and codes for metapopulations and populations, and sample size for morphometric analysis" pageId="9" pageNumber="828">Tables 1</tableCitation>
, 
<tableCitation id="C6EF3AADA067FFC7FE28F8A3D6E4F8B4" box="[412,428,1820,1842]" captionStart="Table 2" captionStartId="4.[144,208,198,217]" captionText="Table 2. DNA voucher no., Locality, GenBank accession no. and location of DNA voucher specimen (FMNH, Finland) of Merodon avidus A and Merodon avidus B sensu Milankov et al., 2001" pageId="9" pageNumber="828">2</tableCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD20F16A067FFC7FF08F885D359FA66" blockId="9.[164,779,1299,1903]" lastBlockId="9.[826,1441,1299,1505]" pageId="9" pageNumber="828">
Wing size (
<emphasis id="B919D304A067FFC7FEE6F884D62AF8D6" box="[338,354,1851,1872]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="828">F</emphasis>
<subScript id="17E90D53A067FFC7FED7F8FCD6D9F8D7" attach="left" box="[355,401,1859,1873]" fontSize="5" pageId="9" pageNumber="828">(2,498)</subScript>
= 65.57, 
<emphasis id="B919D304A067FFC7FDB0F884D55CF8D6" box="[516,532,1851,1872]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="828">P</emphasis>
&lt;0.001) and shape (Wilks’ L = 0.49; 
<emphasis id="B919D304A067FFC7FEDCF8E6D630F8E8" box="[360,376,1881,1902]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="828">F</emphasis>
<subScript id="17E90D53A067FFC7FECDF8DED6E7F8E9" attach="left" box="[377,431,1889,1903]" fontSize="5" pageId="9" pageNumber="828">(32,966)</subScript>
= 12.75; 
<emphasis id="B919D304A067FFC7FDADF8E6D561F8E8" box="[537,553,1881,1902]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="828">P</emphasis>
&lt;0.000) of two the available specimens from 
<collectingCountry id="F37A4F86A067FFC7FBD6FAACD3ECFAAF" box="[1122,1188,1299,1321]" name="Spain" pageId="9" pageNumber="828">Spain</collectingCountry>
were distinctly different from both 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D7495A067FFC7FC55FA8CD326FAC1" authority="A" box="[993,1134,1330,1352]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Merodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="822" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="avidus">
<emphasis id="B919D304A067FFC7FC55FA8CD31BFAC1" box="[993,1107,1330,1352]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="828">M. avidus</emphasis>
A
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D7495A067FFC7FB1CFA8CD27EFAC1" authority="B" box="[1192,1334,1330,1352]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Merodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="822" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="avidus">
<emphasis id="B919D304A067FFC7FB1CFA8CD253FAC1" box="[1192,1307,1330,1352]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="828">M. avidus</emphasis>
B
</taxonomicName>
from the Balkan Peninsula. COI mtDNA sequence divergences between the Balkan and Spanish clades ranged from 4.93 to 6.0 (
<tableCitation id="C6EF3AADA067FFC7FC7CFA31D356FA22" box="[968,1054,1422,1444]" captionStart="Table 4" captionStartId="12.[144,208,671,692]" captionText="Table 4. Number of fixed differences (lower matrix) and uncorrected (P; %) distance matrix for haplotypes of Merodon bicolor (XVIII, XIX, XX) and the Merodon avidus taxa (M. avidus A, M. avidus B in bold, common haplotypes underlined) (*sequences obtained by J+I primers; Lunt et al., 1996)" pageId="9" pageNumber="828">Table 4</tableCitation>
). Thus, wing morphometrics and COI mtDNA haplotypes allowed clear delineation of these cryptic taxa.
</paragraph>
